Program: Last Word
Title: Jean McFarlane, Phillip Tobias, Warda Al Jazairia, Barry Unsworth and Lee Rich
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01jrqrh
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 17 Jun 2012
Matthew Bannister on Lady Jean McFarlane who transformed the way nurses are trained in the UK; Philip Tobias, the South African paleoanthropologist who carried out pioneering research into the evolution of human beings - and fought apartheid; The North African diva Warda Al-Jazairia The Booker prize winning historical novelist Barry Unsworth And the influential American TV producer Lee Rich. His Lorimar Company brought us the Waltons and Dallas. Show less